ntain 40 mph (64 km/h)','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(2997,2,'39-299-1','3. Type the number on the phone using your mouse','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(2998,2,'39-299-7','3. Type the number on the phone','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(2999,2,'39-300-1','Now try to do both at the same time','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3000,2,'34-5','mph','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3001,2,'34-6','km/h','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3002,2,'34-7','meters','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3003,2,'34-8','feet','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3004,2,'31-241-1','Which statement best represents the main point of the exercise you just completed?','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3005,2,'33-242-1','it is difficult to maintain concentration while multitasking','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3006,2,'33-243-1','it is difficult to dial a phone number while driving','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3007,2,'33-244-1','it is more difficult to drive a car than it is to dial a phone number','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3008,2,'33-245-1','it is difficult to maintain a consistent speed while multitasking','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3009,2,'33-246-1','it is difficult to multitask without impacting performance','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3010,2,'52-237-1','Why is multitasking impossible?','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3011,2,'53-237-1','Multitasking cannot be done because your brain is not designed to efficiently juggle two or more tasks at a time. In fact, the term multitasking is not accurate. A more accurate phrase is task switching.','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3012,2,'52-238-1','Single task focus','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3013,2,'53-238-1','As a person pursues a single goal, both sides of the brain focus on the task at hand.','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3014,2,'52-239-1','Adding activities','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3015,2,'53-239-1','Many people assume that the brain is able to divide its attention to focus on multiple tasks simultaneously.','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3016,2,'52-240-1','Task switching','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3017,2,'53-240-1','Instead, the brain rapidly switches focus between the two tasks, with one task being suspended while the other is being focused on.','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3018,2,'31-247-1','When your brain tries to multitask, it divides its attention to focus on each task simultaneously.','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3019,2,'33-248-1','TRUE','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3020,2,'33-249-1','FALSE','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3021,2,'52-251-1','How does multitasking affect performance?','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3022,2,'53-251-1','When you try to multitask, each task takes longer to complete, and more errors are made, than if you focused on a single task at a time.','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3023,2,'52-252-1','Multitasking in action','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3024,2,'53-252-1','In this example, watch as 2 people complete 2 tasks. Person A will focus on a single task at a time, and Person B will attempt to multitask.','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3025,2,'52-253-1','Multitasking in action','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3026,2,'53-253-1','Both participants start Task 1 at the same time.','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3027,2,'52-254-1','Goal shifting','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3028,2,'53-254-1','Person B decides to move from one task to another. This is called goal shifting, and it is the first step the brain must take in order to switch tasks.','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3029,2,'52-255-1','Rule activation','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3030,2,'53-255-1','Next, the brain turns off the rules for the first task, and turns on the rules it needs to complete the next one. This is called rule activation.','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3031,2,'52-256-1','The task switches','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3032,2,'53-256-1','After shifting goals and activating new rules, Person B now begins Task 2. Meanwhile, Person A has not needed these processes.','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3033,2,'52-257-1','Look at what happened','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(3034,2,'53-257-1','Shifting goals and activating new rules doe