water. Large amounts of water, such as a flooded road, diminish the effectiveness of brakes.','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32167,2,'3-1259-1','Even when the sky is clear, natural hazards can create significant dangers for drivers. At some angles, bright sunshine can temporarily blind motorists in traffic. High winds restrict steering ability and can push vehicles off course, particularly large trucks. Crosswinds also create air turbulence when entering or leaving tunnels or other covered areas. Another problem is heat, which can make drivers tired or take a heavy toll on vehicles’ engines. ','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32168,2,'2-1259-1','Veiled Threats','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32169,2,'2-1260-1','Dangerous Neglect','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32170,2,'3-1260-1','Dangerous weather exposes drivers to hazards that are out of their control, yet some refuse to adjust to the conditions despite the risk. These motorists drive too fast, leave insufficient room around other vehicles, or fail to prepare their vehicles for changes in season. Poor choices make it difficult to drive safely in adverse conditions, and they can leave drivers stranded, injured in a crash or worse. ','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32171,2,'33-1310-1','fog','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32172,2,'33-1309-1','wind','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32173,2,'33-1311-1','none of the above are correct','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32174,2,'2-1261-1','Prepare for the Worst','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32175,2,'3-1261-1','It is best to avoid traveling in bad weather altogether. If you must head out, listen to weather reports, observe conditions around you continuously, and bring an emergency kit that includes:\n• Non-perishable food and bottled water.\n• Reflective clothing.\n• A blanket and extra pair of shoes.\n• A first-aid kit and seatbelt cutter.\n• Road maps.\n• Antifreeze liquid and jumper cables.\n• Warning triangles, warning lights or road flares.\n• A fire extinguisher.','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32176,2,'31-1264-1','What is hydroplaning?','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32177,2,'114-1263-1','assessment','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32178,2,'33-1265-1','the heavy splash that larger vehicles can produce in wet weather','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32179,2,'33-1266-1','when tires lose contact with the road surface and glide on top of water','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32180,2,'33-1267-1','storm runoff caused by heavy rainfall','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32181,2,'33-1268-1','an aggressive driving behavior during bad weather','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32182,2,'33-1269-1','none of the above are correct','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32183,2,'31-1270-1','Which of the following statements is true?','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32184,2,'33-1271-1','weather-related hazards pose a risk only when it is raining','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32185,2,'33-1272-1','weather-related hazards pose a risk only in foggy conditions','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32186,2,'33-1274-1','weather-related hazards pose a risk only when roads flood','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32187,2,'33-1273-1','weather-related hazards can affect driving even under clear skies','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32188,2,'33-1275-1','none of the above statements are true','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32189,2,'31-1294-1','If you end up in a skid from hydroplaning, you should ','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32190,2,'33-1295-1','take your foot off the accelerator and turn sharply away from the skid ','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32191,2,'33-1297-1','brake firmly and turn sharply away from the skid','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32192,2,'33-1296-1','take your foot off the accelerator and steer towards the direction you want to go','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32193,2,'33-1298-1','brake firmly and steer towards the direction you want to go','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32194,2,'33-1299-1','take your foot off the accelerator and brake firmly','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(32195,2,'31-1300-1','To maneuver safely in bad weather, what should you remember?','en',NULL,NULL,'US