'US',NULL),(33178,2,'3-571-1','Distracted driving is any non-driving activity that takes drivers’ hands off the wheel, their eyes off the road or their mind off driving. Cell phones are not the only distractions drivers face; even simple tasks can interfere with the ability to safely operate a vehicle, including:\n• Eating or drinking.\n• Personal grooming.\n• Adjusting vehicle controls or navigational units.\n• Fiddling with entertainment systems.\n• Talking with passengers.','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(33179,2,'3-570-1','Despite the growing evidence linking distractions to dangerous driving, far too many motorists still find themselves distracted behind the wheel. They combine other tasks with driving because they believe they can multitask, and mobile technology devices only increase the temptation. While distractions alone may not cause collisions, distracted drivers commit serious errors that significantly increase their crash risk. ','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(33180,2,'2-569-1','Deadly Distractions','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(33181,2,'3-569-1','In this module, participants will learn:\n1.  What distracted driving means and why it is dangerous.\n2.  Why multitasking while driving is a myth.\n3.  Ways to stay focused behind the wheel.','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(33182,2,'2-573-1','Dialing Up Disaster','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(33183,2,'2-574-1','Full Attention Required','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(33184,2,'3-574-1','Driving already involves four areas of the brain, so drivers have no room to juggle additional tasks. Poor decisions and bad habits place everyone at risk, so do not treat driving as idle time. Keeping roads safe and staying alive are not unproductive activities; they are every driver’s responsibility.','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(33185,2,'31-1325-1','Which of the following statements is true?','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(33186,2,'33-1326-1','cell phones are just one of the distractions drivers might face','en',NULL,NULL,'US',NULL),(33187,2,'33-1327-1',