 a driver with a blood alcohol content of 0.05%. If you extend your awake time to 24 hours, you are as likely to crash as a driver with a BAC of 0.10%.','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33335,2,'33-550-1','drowsy drivers are not impaired drivers','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33336,2,'33-551-1','all of the above statements are true','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33337,2,'2-503-1','Under the Influence of Fatigue','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33338,2,'3-503-1','Drowsy drivers make dangerous mistakes such as:\n• Failing to maintain a steady and appropriate speed.\n• Drifting from lane to lane.\n• Following vehicles too closely.\n• Missing traffic signs and exits.','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33339,2,'31-512-1','What are microsleeps?','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33340,2,'33-513-1','naps taken after you pull off to the side of the road','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33341,2,'33-514-1','sleep episodes lasting from a fraction of a second to several seconds','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33342,2,'33-515-1','multiple short rests on long trips','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33343,2,'31-518-1','If you drive drowsy, you may experience which of the following?','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33344,2,'33-516-1','sleep episodes lasting from 5 to 10 minutes','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33345,2,'33-517-1','the extra sleep you get after hitting the snooze button on your alarm','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33346,2,'33-519-1','brief episodes of sleep','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33347,2,'33-520-1','blurred vision, or trouble keeping your eyes open or your head up','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33348,2,'33-521-1','wandering thoughts or daydreaming','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33349,2,'33-523-1','all of the above are correct','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33350,2,'33-522-1','impaired judgment','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33351,2,'31-524-1','Which of the following statements is true?','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33352,2,'33-526-1','opening a window is the best way to avoid drowsiness while driving','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33353