 to avoid fail-to-give-way collisions.\n','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33480,2,'2-700-1','Avoiding Fail-to-Give-Way Collisions','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33481,2,'2-701-1','Common Collisions','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33482,2,'2-702-1','Conflict Points','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33483,2,'3-701-1','Failure to give way is a frequent cause of crashes on roads and highways, occurring when drivers misjudge the actions of other road users at intersections, while changing lanes, or when merging into traffic. Though easily preventable, fail-to-give-way crashes cause many deaths on Asian roads every year.','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33484,2,'3-703-1','When critical details about priority are missing or hidden from view, it becomes harder to anticipate the choices other road users make. Parked vehicles, blind spots and even the landscape can conceal important information, such as traffic signs or approaching hazards. Right-of-way rules establish priority for special vehicles and road users, and when drivers ignore them, they put everyone at risk.','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33485,2,'3-702-1','Priority rules are critical at intersections, but not all drivers follow them. Up to 40% of drivers injured or killed in intersection crashes commit a driving infraction, such as failing to give way. Turning left always presents a risk, as some drivers misjudge vehicle speeds and turn before it is safe. Drivers speeding or running red lights harm far too many road users every year.','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33486,2,'2-703-1','Missing Critical Details','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33487,2,'3-704-1','Fail-to-give-way crashes often happen when drivers:\n• Forget or are unfamiliar with the rules.\n• Fail to scan the roadway for signs or traffic.\n• Do not check mirrors and blind spots for hazards.\n• Signal late or not at all.\n• Let distractions impair their judgment and perception.\n• Are rushed or overconfident, leading to dangerous choices on the road.','en',NULL,NULL,'MM',NULL),(33488,